-- Fluor Agrees to Build 125-Megawatt Solar Plant in Arizona for LS Power
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2012-01-31T16:21:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/fluor-agrees-to-build-125-megawatt-solar-plant-in-arizona-for-ls-power.html
Fluor Corp. (FLR) , the U.S.’s largest
publicly traded engineering and construction company, will build
a 125-megawatt solar plant in Maricopa County,  Arizona .  LS Power Group awarded Fluor a lump-sum contract to build
the plant, the Irving, Texas-based construction company said
today in a statement that didn’t give a price. Fluor included
the deal in its fourth-quarter backlog.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in New York at 
